 	<li>Third-hand smoke is what one smells when a smoker gets in an elevator after going outside for a cigarette. The stuff is so toxic that your brain is telling you â€˜GET AWAYâ€™.</li>
 	<li>Among the substance in third-hand smoke are, Hydrogen cyanide used in chemical weapons, Butane â€“ used in lighter fluid, Arsenic, lead, carbon monoxide &amp; polonium-210 (Radio active carcinogen).</li>
